cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper deals with the visualization of recommendations and clusters, which is a common topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of recommending similar items based on user preferences. The use of maps as a visualization tool falls under the category of social and information visualization (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach in visualizing similarities and recommendations arising from TV shows and music selections, which could fall under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
